<main>

	<h1 class="mb-4">Videos</h1>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead">Wharton School commencement speech</p>
		<p>&ldquo;You are part of&nbsp;this astonishing journey: the progress of&nbsp;civilization in&nbsp;the Universe.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>In&nbsp;1990, Yuri was the first student from the Soviet Union to&nbsp;be&nbsp;admitted to&nbsp;a&nbsp;US business school&nbsp;&ndash; Wharton School, at&nbsp;the University of&nbsp;Pennsylvania. In&nbsp;2016, he&nbsp;was invited back to&nbsp;give the commencement speech. He&nbsp;told his story, focusing on&nbsp;the importance, for both individuals and humanity at&nbsp;large, of&nbsp;&ldquo;looking beyond the horizon.&rdquo;</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZlwMm5XehPg?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead">Presenting Breakthrough Starshot at&nbsp;Code 2016</p>
		<p>&ldquo;Our generation is&nbsp;the first one ever to&nbsp;have the opportunity to&nbsp;achieve interstellar travel&rdquo;.</p>
		<p>At&nbsp;the annual Code conference on&nbsp;technology in&nbsp;2016, Yuri presented Breakthrough Starshot, the first practical program to&nbsp;reach another star, using a&nbsp;gram-scale robotic space probe.</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CFDSsrxWxlQ?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead">Breakthrough Initiatives launch</p>
		<p>&ldquo;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;time to&nbsp;open our eyes, our ears, and our minds to&nbsp;the cosmos.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>On&nbsp;July&nbsp;20, 2015, Yuri was joined by&nbsp;Steven Hawking, Lord Martin Rees, Frank Drake and other luminaries at&nbsp;London&rsquo;s historic Royal Society to&nbsp;launch the Breakthrough Initiatives, a&nbsp;major new set of&nbsp;programs in&nbsp;astronomy and space science, including Breakthrough Listen, a&nbsp;$100m search for evidence of&nbsp;civilizations beyond Earth.</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/f9pqgqhVrgk?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">
		<p class="lead">Breakthrough Starshot launch</p>
		<p>&ldquo;For the first time in&nbsp;human history, we&nbsp;can do&nbsp;more than just gaze at&nbsp;the stars. We&nbsp;can actually reach them.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>On&nbsp;12&nbsp;April, 2016, Yuri was joined by&nbsp;Stephen Hawking, Freeman Dyson, Mae Jemison, Avi Loeb and Pete Worden at&nbsp;the One World Center in&nbsp;New York City, where they announced Breakthrough Starshot, a&nbsp;$100m research and development program to&nbsp;build the first ever space probe capable of&nbsp;reaching another star within a&nbsp;generation. Mark Zuckerberg joined Yuri and Professor Hawking on&nbsp;the program&rsquo;s Board.</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/c7VPHGjT8A4?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="mb-5">

		<p class="lead">Breakthrough Prize ceremony speeches</p>

		<p>&ldquo;Stephen Hawking&rsquo;s passion for science is&nbsp;indestructible.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>Yuri presented Stephen Hawking with the inaugural Special Prize in&nbsp;Fundamental Physics at&nbsp;a&nbsp;ceremony in&nbsp;Geneva in&nbsp;2013.</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/xawkTBAcHCA?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>

		<p>&ldquo;The quest for knowledge is&nbsp;what fires our laureates... and when they find&nbsp;it, it&nbsp;elevates&nbsp;us all.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>At&nbsp;the 2014&nbsp;ceremony, Yuri and Mark Zuckerberg announced their sponsorship of&nbsp;a&nbsp;new Breakthrough Prize in&nbsp;Mathematics.</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SzaRqmpFKeM?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>

		<p>&ldquo;A&nbsp;few billion years ago, someone released the brakes and stepped on&nbsp;the gas pedal.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>Yuri and Eddie Redmayne announced the 2015 Breakthrough Prize in&nbsp;Fundamental Physics, awarded to&nbsp;two teams of&nbsp;astronomers who discovered that the expansion of&nbsp;the Universe is&nbsp;accelerating.</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QYKoDwNJlHo?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>

		<p>&lsquo;Migration and exodus&nbsp;&ndash; struggle and survival&nbsp;&ndash; love and war.&ldquo;</p>
		<p>At&nbsp;the 2016&nbsp;ceremony, Yuri and Christina Aguilera presented the Breakthrough Prize in&nbsp;Life Sciences to&nbsp;Swedish scientist Svante P&auml;&auml;bo, a&nbsp;pioneer of&nbsp;paleogenetics, which de-codes the genomes of&nbsp;fossilized organisms&nbsp;&ndash; including our own ancestors&nbsp;&ndash; and reveals their stories.</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/bN1F_03MMyY?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>

		<p>&ldquo;The detection of&nbsp;two black holes colliding a&nbsp;billion years ago belongs to&nbsp;all humanity.&rdquo;</p>
		<p>Yuri and Sienna Miller announced the 2017 Special Breakthrough Prize in&nbsp;Fundamental Physics for the LIGO team, which had succeeded in&nbsp;detecting gravitational waves.</p>
		<div class="video">
			<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/RP4Okzy_wAM?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>

	</div>

